.TH "vfs_fstat" 9 "vfs_fstat" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vfs_fstat \- Get the basic attributes by file descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vfs_fstat
.BI "(int fd "  ","
.BI "struct kstat *stat "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fd" 12
The file descriptor referring to the file of interest
.IP "stat" 12
The result structure to fill in.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is a wrapper around \fBvfs_getattr\fP.  The main difference is
that it uses a file descriptor to determine the file location.

0 will be returned on success, and a -ve error code if unsuccessful.
